    <h2 class="artic-word-heading">About category and subcategory</h2>
    <p>In IT Service Management (ITSM), the category is an important dimension for grouping and managing service requests, incidents, and problems. A well-defined categorization system helps quickly locate the source of an issue, assign appropriate technical support, and optimize the overall service process.</p>
    <hr/>
    <h2>1. The Purpose of Categories</h2>
    <p>
        <strong>Facilitates quick ticket assignment</strong><br>
        Based on the category, the system can automatically assign tickets to the corresponding technical team, improving response efficiency.
    </p>

    <p>
        <strong>Data analysis and reporting</strong><br>
        By categorizing tickets, the system can analyze which problems occur most frequently, providing data support for continuous improvement.
    </p>

    <p>
        <strong>Enhances user experience</strong><br>
        When users select the correct category while submitting tickets, it helps the issue get resolved faster.
    </p>
